column1: Congress ' ammunition : Prohibitive measures  Both the House and Senate bills would prohibit the manufacture or transfer of weapons with detachable magazines and any two of these : -- Folding or telescopic stock -- Pistol grip on a rifle -- Bayonet mount -- Flash suppressor or threaded barrel to accommodate a suppressor or other accessories -- Grenade launcher -- Barrel shroud allowing shooter to hold a pistol with both hands -- Pistols with magazines outside grip -- Shotguns with fixed magazines holding more than five rounds -- Handguns weighing 50 ounces or more unloaded The House bill also : -- Bans ammunition magazines that hold more than 10 rounds -- Exempts 650 other guns -- Doubles the penalty to 10 years from 5 years for anyone who uses a banned weapon in a violent or drug trafficking crime -- Prohibits the transfer of such a weapon unless the recipient has filled out a tracking form -- Calls for the U.S. attorney general to study the effect of the ban
